Tip for your presentation:
In your hackathon video or write-up, you can use the dashboard screenshot to explain:

1. THE MULTI-AGENT TAX: Point to the "Coordination Efficiency" (purple) line. Explain how Prism penalizes redundant communication, forcing agents to use the shared World Model instead of spamming search queries.
2. ATOMIC FAULT TOLERANCE: Point to the "Atomic Health" (orange) line. Notice the dips where the environment injected a "mid-task failure." Explain how the agent used 'checkpoint' and 'rollback' to recover its state without losing progress.
3. DENSE REWARD SIGNALS: Show the "Reward Trajectory" chart. Explain that unlike standard "success/fail" environments, Prism provides a per-step 5-component vector that makes reliability a trainable signal.
4. MODEL AGNOSTICISM: Show the "Model Comparison" chart. This proves your environment works across Llama, Gemini, and OpenAI, providing a standardized benchmark for LLM agent reliability.

"Our environment (Prism) uses a multi-agent coordination reward. Here we see an agent that managed to run tests and verify, but failed to properly document the fix (write_fix), leading to a lower overall reward. Our RL training loop specifically targets these coordination gaps."


